* identity_accept_regression.dts
* AI-agent local-security accept cycle (AIF-045 2c) — repeatable, self-cleaning.
*
* Admits a throwaway AI agent, proves the resolver denies a requires-approval action,
* the owner grants it (scoped + time-boxed) so the resolver flips to ALLOW, ungrants so
* it flips back to DENY, then deletes the agent. Deterministic (no grant-id lookups) and
* re-runnable: it deletes any leftover agent up front and cleans up at the end.
*
* Expected (grep between BEGIN/END):
*   USER CAN git.commit FOR member.ai.regbot : DENY     (pre-grant)
*   USER CAN git.commit FOR member.ai.regbot : ALLOW    (granted)
*   USER CAN git.commit FOR member.ai.regbot : DENY     (ungranted)
*   USER DELETE: removed member 'member.ai.regbot'
*
* Mutates only the identity catalog under data/metadata/identity (adds then removes a
* throwaway member); leaves the seeded members/roles/permissions intact.
*
* Run:  REGRESSION RUN IDENTITY_ACCEPT
*   or: DOTSCRIPT dottalkpp/data/scripts/dotscript/identity_accept_regression.dts

SET ECHO OFF
STOP_ON_ERROR OFF

FORMULA "IDENTITY-ACCEPT-REGRESSION-BEGIN"
USER AS
USER DELETE member.ai.regbot
FORMULA "admit a throwaway AI agent:"
USER ADD member.ai.regbot AI role.ai_partner
FORMULA "expect DENY (AI partner is not eligible for git.commit):"
USER CAN git.commit FOR member.ai.regbot
FORMULA "owner grants the scoped, time-boxed permission:"
USER GRANT git.commit TO member.ai.regbot
FORMULA "expect ALLOW (override eligibility + live grant):"
USER CAN git.commit FOR member.ai.regbot
FORMULA "owner withdraws it:"
USER UNGRANT git.commit FROM member.ai.regbot
FORMULA "expect DENY (capability withdrawn):"
USER CAN git.commit FOR member.ai.regbot
FORMULA "clean up the throwaway agent:"
USER DELETE member.ai.regbot
FORMULA "IDENTITY-ACCEPT-REGRESSION-END"
